'''Noun''' Term of address

When refering to someone high in society, like an emperor of a king, you would usually say 'Your Excellency' 
It is refering to the greatnes of the person and showing respect, it is an archaic expression, and today you would hear expressions such as 'Your [[Highness]]' '[[Sir]]' or '[[Ma'am]]'

''I am honoured to be in you're presence, Your Excellency!''

